<p><strong>Breaking: Uzodinma Wins&nbsp;</strong><strong>Orlu, Ideato North,&nbsp;</strong><strong>Ohaji/Igbema, Ihite/IUboma,&nbsp;</strong><strong>Mbaitoli&nbsp;</strong><strong>LGs</strong></p>



<p>Governor Hope Uzodinma of the All Progressives Congress has won&nbsp;&nbsp;the governorship election in Orlu, Ideato North,&nbsp;Ohaji/Igbema, Ihite/IUboma and&nbsp;Mbaitoli Local Government Areas of the state.</p>



<p>In the results announced at the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) State Collation Centre in Owerri Sunday morning, Governor Uzodinma scored the highest votes in each of the five local governments, beating his closest rivals, the candidates of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP),&nbsp;&nbsp;Sam Anyanwu, and Labour Party, Athan Achonu with huge margins.</p>



